            <title>[KAFKA-4042] DistributedHerder thread can die because of connector &amp; task lifecycle exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4042</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As one example, there isn&apos;t exception handling in &lt;tt&gt;DistributedHerder.startConnector()&lt;/tt&gt; or the call-chain for it originating in the &lt;tt&gt;tick()&lt;/tt&gt; on the herder thread, and it can throw an exception because of a bad class name in the connector config. (report of issue in wild: &lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/d/msg/confluent-platform/EnleFnXpZCU/3B_gRxsRAgAJ&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://groups.google.com/d/msg/confluent-platform/EnleFnXpZCU/3B_gRxsRAgAJ&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
